{% import "_includes/forms" as forms %}

<h2>Global Field Fallbacks</h2>
{% include 'seo/seo-fieldtype-settings' %}

<hr>

<h2>Field Templates</h2>
<p>To calculate various readability metrics, we need to know how to display the fields. We will only be looking at the
	fields selected in the global readability fields above or the ones selected for the current SEO field, so you don't
	need to worry about filling all the fields out. The plugin will guess how to display any fields that do not have
	specifically defined templates. Any fields that fail to display will be skipped by the checker.</p>
<p>In most cases the basic Twig template code will be enough (this is what the plugin will use as a fallback), but for
	more complex fields such as Matrixes or tables template code is required.</p>
<p>Please include only the most perfunctory of HTML in your template code, remembering that layout is not important,
	while images, headers, and links are. Paragraph tags are also considered. The plugin does not check for Schema (we
	focus on content), so no need to include that.</p>

<table id="debugTable" class="shadow-box editable">
	<thead>
	<tr>
		<th class="header">Name (handle)</th>
		<th class="header">Field Type</th>
		<th class="header">Template</th>
	</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
	{% for field in fields %}
		{% if field.type != 'SEO' %}
			<tr>
				<td style="text-align:left;vertical-align:top;"><label for="fieldTemplates[{{ field.value }}]"><strong>{{ field.label }}</strong> <code>({{ field.value }})</code></label></td>
				<td style="text-align:left;vertical-align:top;"><label for="fieldTemplates[{{ field.value }}]">{{ field.type }}</label></td>
				<td class="textual code">
		<textarea name="fieldTemplates[{{ field.value }}]"
		          id="fieldTemplates[{{ field.value }}]" placeholder="&#123;{ entry.{{ field.value }} }}"
		          oninput="this.style.height='';this.style.height=this.scrollHeight+'px';"
		          rows="1">{{ settings.fieldTemplates is not null ? settings.fieldTemplates[field.value] is defined ? settings.fieldTemplates[field.value] : '{{ entry.'~field.value~' }}' : '{{ entry.'~field.value~' }}' }}</textarea>
				</td>
			</tr>
		{% endif %}
	{% endfor %}
	</tbody>
</table>